ciscoIpMRouteMIB.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIB

revisions.description: Add 32-bit and 64-bit per interface packet counters. These apply to all interfaces, including Point-To-Point types, unlike ifInMulticastPkts etc which only apply to interfaces with multicast at that layer. Also fix import of Unsigned32.

Add ciscoIpMRouteNumberOfEntries. Also add 64-bit counters to represent information for high speed interfaces like OC-192. Deprecate ciscoIpMRouteBps in favour of the 64-bit counter ciscoIpMRouteBps2. ciscoIpMouteMetric deprecated in favour of ciscoIpMouteMetric2 to correctly represent a 32-bit unsigned metric value.
Added MIB support for multicast heartbeat monitoring.
Obsolete ciscoIpMRouteInLimit and replaced with ciscoIpMRouteInLimit2.

ciscoIpMRouteMIB.contactinfo: cisco Systems, Inc. 170 Tasman Drive San Jose, CA EMail: cs-ipmulticast@cisco.com
ciscoIpMRouteMIB.description: The MIB module for management of IP Multicast routing, but independent of the specific multicast routing protocol in use.

ciscoIpMRouteNumberOfEntries.name: ciscoIpMRouteNumberOfEntries
ciscoIpMRouteNumberOfEntries.description: Maintains a count of the number of entries in the ipMRouteTable.

ciscoIpMRouteTable.name: ciscoIpMRouteTable
ciscoIpMRouteTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information for IP datagrams sent by particular sources to the IP multicast groups known to this router. This table is augmented to the ipMRouteTable.

ciscoIpMRouteEntry.name: ciscoIpMRouteEntry
ciscoIpMRouteEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for IP datagrams from a particular source and addressed to a particular IP multicast group address.

ciscoIpMRoutePruneFlag.name: ciscoIpMRoutePruneFlag
ciscoIpMRoutePruneFlag.description: Boolean, indicates whether this route is pruned. A pruned route is one that has an empty outgoing interface list or all interfaces are in Pruned state. A multicast packet that matches a pruned route doesn't get forwarded.

ciscoIpMRouteSparseFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteSparseFlag
ciscoIpMRouteSparseFlag.description: Boolean, indicating PIM multicast routing protocol sparse-mode (versus dense-mode). In sparse-mode, packets are forwarded only out interfaces that have been joined. In dense-mode, they are forwarded out all interfaces that have not been pruned.

ciscoIpMRouteConnectedFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteConnectedFlag
ciscoIpMRouteConnectedFlag.description: Boolean, indicating whether there is a directly connected member for a group attached to the router.

ciscoIpMRouteLocalFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteLocalFlag
ciscoIpMRouteLocalFlag.description: Boolean, indicating whether local system is a member of a group on any interface.

ciscoIpMRouteRegisterFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteRegisterFlag
ciscoIpMRouteRegisterFlag.description: Boolean, indicates whether to send registers for the entry. A first hop router directly connected to a multicast source host, as well as a border router on the boundary of two domains running different multicast routing protocols, encapsulates packets to be sent on the shared tree. This is done until the RP sends Joins back to this router.

ciscoIpMRouteRpFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteRpFlag
ciscoIpMRouteRpFlag.description: Boolean, indicating whether there is a Prune state for this source along the shared tree.

ciscoIpMRouteSptFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteSptFlag
ciscoIpMRouteSptFlag.description: Boolean, indicating whether data is being received on the SPT tree, ie the Shortest Path Tree.

ciscoIpMRouteBps.name: ciscoIpMRouteBps
ciscoIpMRouteBps.description: Bits per second forwarded by this router. This is the sum of all forwarded bits during a 1 second interval. At the end of each second the field is cleared. This object has been superseded by ciscoIpMRouteBps2 (which is the 64-bit version of this object).

ciscoIpMRouteMetric.name: ciscoIpMRouteMetric
ciscoIpMRouteMetric.description: Metric - The best metric heard from Assert messages. This object has been replaced by ciscoIpMRouteMetric2 in order to correctly represent a 32-bit unsigned metric value.

ciscoIpMRouteMetricPreference.name: ciscoIpMRouteMetricPreference
ciscoIpMRouteMetricPreference.description: Metric Preference - The best metric preference heard from Assert messages.

ciscoIpMRouteInLimit.name: ciscoIpMRouteInLimit
ciscoIpMRouteInLimit.description: Incoming interface's limit for rate limiting data traffic, in Kbps. Replaced by ciscoIpMRouteInLimit2.

ciscoIpMRouteLastUsed.name: ciscoIpMRouteLastUsed
ciscoIpMRouteLastUsed.description: How long has it been since the last multicast packet was fastswitched.

ciscoIpMRouteInLimit2.name: ciscoIpMRouteInLimit2
ciscoIpMRouteInLimit2.description: Incoming interface's limit for rate limiting data traffic, in Kbps.

ciscoIpMRouteJoinFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteJoinFlag
ciscoIpMRouteJoinFlag.description: Boolean, indicates whether this route is created due to SPT threshold.

ciscoIpMRouteMsdpFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteMsdpFlag
ciscoIpMRouteMsdpFlag.description: Boolean, indicates whether this route is learned via MSDP.

ciscoIpMRouteProxyJoinFlag.name: ciscoIpMRouteProxyJoinFlag
ciscoIpMRouteProxyJoinFlag.description: Boolean, indicates whether to send join for this entry.

ciscoIpMRoutePkts.name: ciscoIpMRoutePkts
ciscoIpMRoutePkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRoutePkts.

ciscoIpMRouteDifferentInIfPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteDifferentInIfPkts
ciscoIpMRouteDifferentInIfPkts.description: The number of packets which this router has received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, which were not received from the interface indicated by ipMRouteInIfIndex. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteDifferentInIfPackets.

ciscoIpMRouteOctets.name: ciscoIpMRouteOctets
ciscoIpMRouteOctets.description: The number of octets contained in IP datagrams which were received from these sources and addressed to this multicast group address, and which were forwarded by this router. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteOctets.

ciscoIpMRouteBps2.name: ciscoIpMRouteBps2
ciscoIpMRouteBps2.description: Bits per second forwarded by this router. This is the sum of all forwarded bits during a 1 second interval. At the end of each second the field is cleared.

ciscoIpMRouteMetric2.name: ciscoIpMRouteMetric2
ciscoIpMRouteMetric2.description: Metric - The best metric heard from Assert messages.

ciscoIpMRouteNextHopTable.name: ciscoIpMRouteNextHopTable
ciscoIpMRouteNextHopTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing information on the next hops on outgoing interfaces for routing IP multicast datagrams. Each entry is one of a list of next hops on outgoing interfaces for particular sources sending to a particular multicast group address.

ciscoIpMRouteNextHopEntry.name: ciscoIpMRouteNextHopEntry
ciscoIpMRouteNextHopEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) in the list of next hops on outgoing interfaces to which IP multicast datagrams from particular sources to a IP multicast group address are routed.

ciscoIpMRouteNextHopOutLimit.name: ciscoIpMRouteNextHopOutLimit
ciscoIpMRouteNextHopOutLimit.description: An outgoing interface's limit for rate limiting data traffic, in Kbps.

ciscoIpMRouteNextHopMacHdr.name: ciscoIpMRouteNextHopMacHdr
ciscoIpMRouteNextHopMacHdr.description: The data link mac address header for a multicast datagram. Used by IP multicast fastswitching.

ciscoIpMRouteNextHopPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteNextHopPkts
ciscoIpMRouteNextHopPkts.description: The number of packets which have been forwarded using this route. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteNextHopPkts.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatTable.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatTable
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatTable.description: The (conceptual) table listing sets of IP Multicast heartbeat parameters. If no IP Multicast heartbeat is configured, this table would be empty.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatEntry.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatEntry
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) representing a set of IP Multicast heartbeat parameters.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatGroupAddr.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatGroupAddr
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatGroupAddr.description: Multicast group address used to receive heartbeat packets.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatSourceAddr.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatSourceAddr
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatSourceAddr.description: Source address of the last multicast heartbeat packet received.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatInterval.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatInterval
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatInterval.description: Number of seconds in which a Cisco multicast router expects a valid heartBeat packet from a source. This value must be a multiple of 10.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatWindowSize.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatWindowSize
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatWindowSize.description: Number of ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatInterval intervals a Cisco multicast router waits before checking if expected number of heartbeat packets are received or not.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatCount.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatCount
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatCount.description: Number of time intervals where multicast packets were received in the last ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatWindowSize intervals.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatMinimum.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatMinimum
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatMinimum.description: The minimal number of heartbeat packets expected in the last ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatWindowSize intervals. If ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatCount falls below this value, an SNMP trap/notification, if configured, will be sent to the NMS.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatAlertTime.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatAlertTime
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatAlertTime.description: The value of sysUpTime on the most recent occasion at which a missing IP multicast heartbeat condition occured for the group address specified in this entry. If no such condition have occurred since the last re-initialization of the local management subsystem, then this object contains a zero value.

ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatStatus.name: ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatStatus
ciscoIpMRouteHeartBeatStatus.description: This object is used to create a new row or delete an existing row in this table.

ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceTable.name: ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceTable
ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceTable.description: The (conceptual) table containing multicast routing information specific to interfaces. This table augments the ipMRouteInterfaceTable.

ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceEntry.name: ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceEntry
ciscoIpMRouteInterfaceEntry.description: An entry (conceptual row) containing the multicast routing information for a particular interface.

ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastOctets.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastOctets
ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteInterfaceInMcastOctets.

ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastOctets.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastOctets
ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastOctets.description: The number of octets of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of ipMRouteInterfaceOutMcastOctets.

ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastPkts
ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface.

ciscoIpMRouteIfHCInMcastPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfHCInMcastPkts
ciscoIpMRouteIfHCInMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets that have arrived on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of ciscoIpMRouteIfInMcastPkts

ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastPkts
ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface.

ciscoIpMRouteIfHCOutMcastPkts.name: ciscoIpMRouteIfHCOutMcastPkts
ciscoIpMRouteIfHCOutMcastPkts.description: The number of multicast packets that have been sent on the interface. This object is a 64-bit version of ciscoIpMRouteIfOutMcastPkts

ciscoIpMRouteMissingHeartBeats.name: ciscoIpMRouteMissingHeartBeats
ciscoIpMRouteMissingHeartBeats.description: A ciscoIpMRouteMissingHeartBeat is sent if a multicast router with this feature enabled failed to receive configured number of heartbeat packets from heartbeat sources within a configured time interval.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBCompliance.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBCompliance
ciscoIpMRouteMIBCompliance.description: The compliance statement for the cisco IP Multicast MIB. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteComplianceV11R01.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV11R01.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV11R01
ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV11R01.description: The compliance statement for the cisco IP Multicast MIB. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteComplianceV12R00S.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R00S.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R00S
ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R00S.description: The compliance statement for the cisco IP Multicast MIB. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R28S

ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R28S.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R28S
ciscoIpMRouteMIBComplianceV12R28S.description: The compliance statement for the cisco IP Multicast MIB.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroup.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroup
ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IP Multicast routing. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV11R01.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV11R01.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV11R01
ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV11R01.description: A collection of objects to support management of IP Multicast routing. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R00S.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBHeartBeatGroup.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBHeartBeatGroup
ciscoIpMRouteMIBHeartBeatGroup.description: A collection of unconditionally optional objects to support IP Multicast heartbeat monitoring.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R00S.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R00S
ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R00S.description: A collection of objects to support management of IP Multicast routing. Superseded by ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R28S

ciscoIpMRouteMIBNotifGroup.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBNotifGroup
ciscoIpMRouteMIBNotifGroup.description: The collection of IPMroute related notifications.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R28S.name: ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R28S
ciscoIpMRouteMIBGroupV12R28S.description: A collection of objects to support management of IP Multicast routing.

ciscoIpMRouteMIBIfGroup.description: A collection of objects to support management of IP Multicast routing on an interface.
